data.value:
Lyon, the sister city of Sinop, is located in the Rhone-Alpes region of France. The center and capital of the Rhone administration is between Marseille and Paris. Traboules, formerly called Lyon, is on the UNESCO World Heritage List. Lyon brings together 3 universities and students, famous cuisine and gourmets.
In the city consisting of two parts; The classical architecture can be discovered in the historic district called ü Vieux Lyon canlı and the new city section can be explored for the living cultural life. In the second half of the 19th century, the Notre Dame de Fourvière Basilica, built in a dominant position in the city, is one of the symbols of the city. On the streets of Presqusinizile you can sniff the city life, have a chic meal, and then enjoy the bohemian life in the hidden gates of Croix-Rousse.
